This is some of my favorite code so far. I am using fundamental code so I am sure someone else has written this elsewhere though all I really found was written in c as both a pipe and module. All c examples seemed too limited for what I wanted to do and change easily without recompiling. 

httpd.conf
ErrorLog "|/usr/bin/php /github/Apache-Log-PHP-Pipe/logProcess.php >> /var/log/httpd/error_log"

The " >> /var/log/httpd/error_log" is used for simple echo to log, it may be removed and replaced by php's error log function.


